<div id="review_44222414" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/44222414" />
    <a title="Kevin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/142320-kevin"><img alt="Kevin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1588905121p2/142320.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/44222414?book_show_action=true">Jan 24, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kevin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kevin" href="/user/show/142320-kevin">Kevin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/142320-kevin?shelf=weird-stuff">weird-stuff</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer44222414" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11290508751606518232">Published in Japan in 1976, this book turned into a <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7437.Naked_Lunch_The_Restored_Text' title='Naked Lunch The Restored Text by William S. Burroughs' rel='nofollow noopener'>Naked Lunch</a> sort of drug-lit phenom. At times, I felt like the violent sex was a bit overdone and I leaned toward a 3-star rating, but there are enough great sentences and amazing imagery to push it to a 4. Ryu takes a lot of chances here--no sturdy plot, odd moments of melancholy, some repugnant scenes, too many characters--but it comes together more often than not, and I was so intrigued by the end, I went and read all the amazon reviews just</span>
  <span id="freeText11290508751606518232" style="display:none">Published in Japan in 1976, this book turned into a <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7437.Naked_Lunch_The_Restored_Text" title="Naked Lunch The Restored Text by William S. Burroughs" rel="nofollow noopener">Naked Lunch</a> sort of drug-lit phenom. At times, I felt like the violent sex was a bit overdone and I leaned toward a 3-star rating, but there are enough great sentences and amazing imagery to push it to a 4. Ryu takes a lot of chances here--no sturdy plot, odd moments of melancholy, some repugnant scenes, too many characters--but it comes together more often than not, and I was so intrigued by the end, I went and read all the amazon reviews just for fun. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11290508751606518232" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
