<div id="review_3289284015" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3289284015" />
    <a title="Jovana Autumn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41176805-jovana-autumn"><img alt="Jovana Autumn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1618543441p2/41176805.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3289284015?book_show_action=true">Apr 20, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jovana Autumn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jovana Autumn" href="/user/show/41176805-jovana-autumn">Jovana Autumn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41176805-jovana-autumn?shelf=my-read-ebooks">my-read-ebooks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41176805-jovana-autumn?shelf=reviews">reviews</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41176805-jovana-autumn?shelf=read-in-serbian">read-in-serbian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41176805-jovana-autumn?shelf=japanese-writers">japanese-writers</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3289284015" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1749007432027628409">Okay, this book delivers just what it says in the blurb.<br/><br/>We follow a gang of young Japanese men and women and their seemingly empty lives filled with drug abuse, alcohol abuse, and orgies. <br/><br/><i>There’s nothing really happening here. </i><br/><br/>All of them have bad coping mechanisms with life, Ryu (the character) contemplates life the most in this novel. <br/><br/>Don’t get me wrong, the characters are beyond likable, all they think about is what to do next to bring them a bit of excitement in their lives – like partying, </span>
  <span id="freeText1749007432027628409" style="display:none">Okay, this book delivers just what it says in the blurb.<br /><br />We follow a gang of young Japanese men and women and their seemingly empty lives filled with drug abuse, alcohol abuse, and orgies. <br /><br /><i>There’s nothing really happening here. </i><br /><br />All of them have bad coping mechanisms with life, Ryu (the character) contemplates life the most in this novel. <br /><br />Don’t get me wrong, the characters are beyond likable, all they think about is what to do next to bring them a bit of excitement in their lives – like partying, sex or more drugs. Their lives are pretty much non-existent outside of that.<br /><br />And who knew, guess Ryu Murakami isn’t a shit writer, after all, I actually got into the book and was disgusted by a couple of scenes and I had the interest to see what will happen to these characters. So kudos for actually making me feel something out of reading the book.<br /><br /><b>
  <i>Now, after reading the book will you get anything out of it? Well, yes and no.</i>
</b><br /><br />Yes in a sense you will be close to seeing the mind of addicts and people who find comfort in substance abuse – which isn’t pretty at all. These people need help and nobody is providing them with it.<br />And No, there isn’t really a point of the book besides that.<br /><br />Still not something that I will really think about in the future, but it is definitely more memorable than <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17810.In_the_Miso_Soup" title="In the Miso Soup by Ryū Murakami" rel="nofollow noopener">In the Miso Soup</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3392668.Audition" title="Audition by Ryū Murakami" rel="nofollow noopener">Audition</a>. <br />-------------------------------------------------------------<br />Could this be the only Ryu Murakami Book that I actually didn't mind? RTC.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1749007432027628409" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

